subject: ENGLISH
text: Write a composition, not exceeding three foolscap pages, on any one of the following subjects: a. My ambition in life. b. The arguments both for and against any one of the following: vegetarianism, the prefect system, a universal language. c. The school debating or literary or dramatic society as an important factor in education. d. Has the aeroplane been a boon or a bane to mankind? e. Describe a visit by Sir Roger de Coverley to any one of the following: the skating rink, the agricultural show, the public library, the dentist.
